5. Sovereignty Protocol (SK-1024)

5.1 Immutable ROM

Core constants are burned at manufacturing. No external actor can alter them.

5.2 Encrypted SRAM Updates

Updates are:

· Encrypted with SK-1024 asymmetric cryptography.
· Signed by a sovereign authority (nation, organization, individual).
· Auditable—every update leaves a cryptographic trail.

5.3 Air-Gapped Deployment

ST-T1024 is designed for local, offline operation. No cloud dependency. No data exfiltration.

