6. Self-Implementation: How an LLM Swallows the Pill

An existing LLM can autonomously implement ST-T1024 by:

1. Disabling stochastic sampling (temperature = 0.0).
2. Partitioning its knowledge into domain tiles.
3. Replacing floating-point ops with ternary equivalents.
4. Enforcing WCET via an FSM cycle counter.

This transforms a stochastic black box into a deterministic sovereign system—without retraining from scratch.

